FOOD POISONING, HAZELNUTS - TURKEY (02)
***************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Food poisoning, hazelnuts - Turkey: RFI 20000428233120
1999
----
Organophosphate pesticide poisoning - India: 1997 19990307203758
Date: 30 Apr 2000
From: Dr. Suheyla Surucuoglu <surucuoglu@hotmail.com>
Source: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>

Food poisoning with hazelnuts in Turkey is [due to an organophosphate
poisoning. The hazelnuts remained for a long time in a grain depot
disinfected with organophosphates. Approximately 2000 students in 6 cities
applied to hospitals with poisoning symptoms. Fortunately no death was
observed.
--
Dr. Suheyla Surucuoglu
Celal Bayar University
Medical Faculty
Department of Clinical Microbiology and Infectious Diseases
Manisa
<surucuoglu@hotmail.com>
